    • Method Detail

      • decryptTransportedKey

        public CipherAndAuthTag decryptTransportedKey(OmemoElement element,
                                              int keyId)
                                       throws CryptoFailedException,
                                              NoRawSessionException
        Try to decrypt the transported message key using the double ratchet session.
        Parameters:
        element - omemoElement
        keyId - our keyId
        Returns:
        tuple of cipher generated from the unpacked message key and the authtag
        Throws:
        CryptoFailedException - if decryption using the double ratchet fails
        NoRawSessionException - if we have no session, but the element was NOT a PreKeyMessage

      • decryptMessageElement

        public static Message decryptMessageElement(OmemoElement element,
                                            CipherAndAuthTag cipherAndAuthTag)
                                     throws CryptoFailedException
        Use the symmetric key in cipherAndAuthTag to decrypt the payload of the omemoMessage. The decrypted payload will be the body of the returned Message.
        Parameters:
        element - omemoElement containing a payload.
        cipherAndAuthTag - cipher and authentication tag.
        Returns:
        Message containing the decrypted payload in its body.
        Throws:
        CryptoFailedException

      • decryptMessageElement

        public Message decryptMessageElement(OmemoElement element,
                                     int keyId)
                              throws CryptoFailedException,
                                     NoRawSessionException
        Try to decrypt the message. First decrypt the message key using our session with the sender. Second use the decrypted key to decrypt the message. The decrypted content of the 'encrypted'-element becomes the body of the clear text message.
        Parameters:
        element - OmemoElement
        keyId - the key we want to decrypt (usually our own device id)
        Returns:
        message as plaintext
        Throws:
        CryptoFailedException
        NoRawSessionException

      • createCipher

        public abstract T_Ciph createCipher(OmemoDevice contact)
        Create a new SessionCipher used to encrypt/decrypt keys. The cipher typically implements the ratchet and KDF-chains.
        Parameters:
        contact - OmemoDevice
        Returns:
        SessionCipher

      • encryptMessageKey

        public abstract CiphertextTuple encryptMessageKey(byte[] messageKey)
                                           throws CryptoFailedException
        Encrypt a message key for the recipient. This key can be deciphered by the recipient with its corresponding session cipher. The key is then used to decipher the message.
        Parameters:
        messageKey - serialized key to encrypt
        Returns:
        A CiphertextTuple containing the ciphertext and the messageType
        Throws:
        CryptoFailedException

      • decryptMessageKey

        public abstract byte[] decryptMessageKey(byte[] encryptedKey)
                                  throws CryptoFailedException,
                                         NoRawSessionException
        Decrypt a messageKey using our sessionCipher. We can use that key to decipher the actual message. Same as encryptMessageKey, just the other way round.
        Parameters:
        encryptedKey - encrypted key
        Returns:
        serialized decrypted key or null
        Throws:
        CryptoFailedException - when decryption fails.
        NoRawSessionException - when no session was found in the double ratchet library
